  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b9e\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd ; \u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 51 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Easter Sunday attack; 51 people from Kathankudi were also arrested",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Batticaloa Magistrate, Judge Peter Pol, today Tuesday (05) ordered through a video to remand the 51 people who were arrested in Kathankudi area in connection with the Easter Sunday attack and who were trained in Sahran's training camp and who were arrested and kept in remand on suspicion of maintaining contact with him, until the 19th of July.",
        "After the attack that took place on 21st April 2021 last Easter Sunday, 69 people including Sahran's sister and her husband were arrested by people from Kathankudi on the suspicion that they were related to Sahran's group and that they had gone to places like Ambanthotai and Nuwaraeliya for training.",
        "Katankudi police filed a case against those arrested and they were kept in remand.",
        "Saran's sister and her husband's cases were transferred from the Magistrate's Court to the High Court, 5 people were acquitted and 15 people were released on bail, and 51 people were kept under remand in jails like Polonnaruwa, Anudarapuram, Kegala, Badulai, Trincomalee etc.",
        "In this situation today, when this case was taken up for trial in the presence of the Batticaloa Magistrate's Court, the judge ordered that the 51 people in various prisons in the country should be kept in remand until the next 19th through video, considering the situation in which the people in various prisons in the country have not been brought."
      ],
